I notied blocks per second is very slow, only about 2.5 blk/s. But as I saw in other cases, it should be above 50 blk/s

Here is status about my server, OS is Ubuntu 22.04.2 LTS, and hardware is list below: 
* cpu: Intel(R) Xeon(R) CPU E5-2686 v4 @ 2.30GHz (18 cores)
* ram: 128GB
* disk: Disk /dev/sdb: 3.73 TiB, Disk model: Fanxiang FP325T 

And the server runs a erigon node and a lighthouse node. erigon version has updatd to 2.43.  start commend: 
```sh
./erigon --datadir="/node/eth/erigon/"  --private.api.addr=localhost:9070 --http --http.port 8545 --http.addr=10.0.0.0 --http.api=eth,erigon,web3,net,debug,trace,txpool
./lighthouse beacon_node --network mainnet --datadir /node/eth/lighthouse --port 9800 --execution-endpoint http://127.0.0.1:8551 --execution-jwt /node/eth/erigon/jwt.hex
```

There are some interest things: 
1. cpu usage and memory usage is very low. Erigon should use all the momery but only 10G is used. 
 
![图片](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/115340054/236134133-0b8a7112-a260-4802-aee9-36d81ae0bc47.png)

2. After I restart erigon, execute speed would be 15 blk/s, but after a while, it fall back to 2.5 blk/s.
3. Disk usage is low too,  lighthouse will cause some disk writing but erigon will not..

![图片](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/115340054/236135074-d5eab1bf-9a58-4975-875b-a078224987fe.png)

Please help, thanks.
